title: For Trade:  Scar 17s Limited Trial Run
postcontent: In 2010, FN decided to bring the Scar 17s to the civilian market. They made these as limited inital production models. They made limited 16s and 17s. Limited 16s have 7 digit serial numbers, that is how many they produced. The 17s only have 3 digit serial numbers. These are incredibly rare. Mostly only dealers and company heads got their hands on these and still have most of them. That is why less than 100 made it to public hands out of 300 ever produced to my knowledge. I have never seen another come up for sale nor has the few big appraisors I had look at it. They came in a rolling Hardigg Storm case, 2 mags, and a Certificate of Authenticity. The intial production run was the test trial to see how well they would do. Only these were produced at a plant in the US. The same plant they made the ones for the military. After the initial production was released, all production moved to Belgium. So very few of them were made that when I called FN, they could not give me a exact number of how many were sold to the public. This is gun 186 out of all ever made. You won't see another much less one for sale. If you are lucky to see another one... it will be shot. Not brand new. Even has all the tags still on it. This is a great collectors item so dont miss it. Shoot me an offer. No I will not sell for the price of a new one that comes in a cardboard box and one mag that they made a million of. I know what its worth. Or close enough at least. Any other info email me and ill answer to the best of my knowledge. I have had several offers so just email me your best cash or trade offer.
